# GOLive Creator Studio Enhancements & Watch Page Fix

I have successfully resolved the 404 error on the watch page and transformed the upload process into a premium **Creator Studio** experience, incorporating advanced features from YouTube and Twitch.

## 🛠️ Critical Fix: Watch Page 404
The "Page Not Found" error was caused by a recent update in Next.js 16 where dynamic route `params` are now provided as a **Promise**. Accessing `params.id` directly was resulting in an `undefined` ID and triggering the `notFound()` block.

- **Fixed**: [app/watch/[id]/page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Walt%20&%20Carter/.gemini/antigravity/playground/sonic-zenith/app/watch/%5Bid%5D/page.tsx) now properly awaits the `params` before querying Supabase.
- **Verification**: Local debug scripts confirmed the video data exists and is now accessible via the server query.

## 🚀 Creator Studio Enhancements

### 1. Advanced Upload Dashboard
The upload page has been refactored to provide a professional, identity-focused experience.

- **Identity Header**: Added an "Uploading as" block with the creator's avatar and verification badge to prevent accidental account mismatches.
- **Ecosystem Controls**: Added a new "Advanced Creator Options" section with premium toggles:
  - **AI Clipping**: Creators can now enable or disable the ability for others to generate Shorts from their content.
  - **Comment Toggles**: Per-video control to enable or disable community discussions.
  - **License Management**: Choose between Standard and Creative Commons licenses.
- **State Persistence**: These settings are now saved directly to the Supabase database.

### 2. Backend & Frontend Enforcement
- **AI Studio API**: Updated the `clip` endpoint to honor the `allow_clipping` flag. If a creator disables clipping, the API will refuse the request (403 Forbidden).
- **Watch UI**: The comment section now dynamically hides and shows based on the `allow_comments` flag, displaying a "Comments are turned off" message when disabled.

## 📦 Technical Details
- **Database**: 5 new columns added to the `videos` table (`allow_clipping`, `allow_comments`, [visibility](file:///C:/GOLive/app/studio/dashboard/page.tsx#124-129), `scheduled_for`, `license`).
- **Types**: Extended the global [Video](file:///C:/GOLive/types/index.ts#15-40) TypeScript interface for full type safety.
- **Build**: Successfully validated with `npm run build`.

